  "prompt": "How do I change my Google default account?",
  "response": "To change your default Google account, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to myaccount.google.com\n\n2. Click on your profile picture/initial in the top right corner\n\n3. Select the account you want to make default from the list\n\n4. If you want to add a new account first:\n- Click \"Add another account\"\n- Sign in with those credentials\n\n5. To set a specific account as default:\n- Desktop: Click on your profile picture\n- Select the desired account\n- Choose \"Use this account\" or \"Always use this account\"\n\n6. On mobile devices:\n- Open Google app or Gmail\n- Tap your profile picture\n- Select the account you want to use\n\n7. For Chrome browser:\n- Click your profile picture\n- Select the desired account\n- Click \"Switch to this account\"\n\nRemember that changing default accounts might affect multiple Google services like Gmail, YouTube, Drive, and others. The process can vary slightly depending on the specific device or platform you're using.\n\nPro tip: You can also manage your accounts in Google's Account Settings under \"Accounts & Import\" section.",
